==English==

===Etymology===
Spokesmen for the {{w|Royal Society of London}} first coined this expression to describe the outflow of scientists and technologists to the United States and Canada in the early 1950s.

===Pronunciation===
{{wikipedia}}
* {{enPR|brānʹ-drān}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[migration]] of [[educated]] or [[talented]] people from less economically [[advanced]] areas to more economically advanced areas, especially to large cities or richer countries.
#: {{ant|en|brain gain}}
# {{lb|en|medicine|informal}} A [[Jackson-Pratt drain]].

